metadata.name: Miniscapes #135
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: VOYAGERS #220
metadata.description:
Generative animated painting made from looping gestures in a virtual void.

Voyagers is an exploration of automated gestures and screenspace layering effects. Each brush stroke sweeps through the canvas leaving a trail of color that either disappears or mixes with adjacent colors. The image slowly builds up to achieve an equilibrium between the rhythm of the gestures and the interaction of color values. These colors are quantized and dithered to produce chunky, textured, blocks of light that reify the materiality of the screen and the pixel. Two aspect ratios are possible, each with its own material relationship to screen-based work, 1:1 and 4:3 (vertical).

Press 's' to save looping animated GIF (live mode only).
Press 'p' to pause the animation.
Press 'c' to capture a single frame.
Made with P5.js and GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

metadata.name: Turbulence #324
metadata.description:
Swirly shapes are rendered by passes of poisson samples of a warped noise field. The noise shifts with each pass, creating a layered effect. 

Dense editions may take over 2 minutes to draw fully.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.

Press â€™sâ€™ to save a screenshot. Image size is 928x1200px
Press â€™pâ€™ to pause/resume at any time during the drawing.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a not 1:1 variation of your edition at a resolution up to 3,000 px.

Common:
- 43 set palettes plus many more with combinations
- 3 color distribution methods
- 50/50 dark
- 50/50 monochrome with bright highlights 
- 3 drawing styles: lines, points, colored pencils
- 5 noises effects: full screen, distance from center, distance from bottom, horizontal center, vertical center, random circles, 3,5, or 7 horizontal and vertical bars
- Poisson point distribution based on set layers or the noise value

Rare
- 15% chance of a dark monochrome with gold strands

metadata.name: The Space Inside #61
metadata.description:
Points fill in shapes on a warped noise field. The resulting images range from soft water colors to distorted, pixelated CRT screens. 

The image is drawn at 3000x3000px and scaled to the browser size. 

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press â€™sâ€™ to save a screenshot. Image size is 3000x3000px
Press â€™pâ€™ to pause/resume.

Features:
- Two palette sets
- Light or dark background
- 70% color image, 30% monochrome
- Various combinations of circles and rectangles
- All rectangles 
- 7 types of shapes: random circles, packed circles, checkerboard, orbs, ring, spiral, checkerboard and orbs
- Rectangles snap to a grid
- Fuzzy lines connected groups of drawing points
- Fuzzy lines around the dots
- Bright border on the shapes

Rare

metadata.name: Dencity #28
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with â¤ï¸, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Morning Mist #260
square haze [86] #57
metadata.description:
Finally it is! Another one piece from square haze collection. This time it is generative fxhash item that represents aesthetics compilation found during previous pieces research on hic et nunc with some improvements discovered during fxhash adaptation. There are some features that controls generated token appearance:
- squareMode: different settings that determine algorithms used to create piece
- colorTheme: one of the best color palettes from the internet
- colorPicker: function used to select color schemes for grid mode
- grid: amount of splits in master square
- colorShift: step that determines how colors iterated in sub-squares (doesn't affect black and white squares)
- padding: yes
- bgIndex: sometimes it adds some vibe to the whole image
- isSiblings: probably the most awful part of the internal that looks great
- law: as it is normal or uniform, the hash will choose
- noiseChance: probability of new created square to became noisy one
- patternChance: the same as noise but with patttterns
- spread: something like dispersion for normal distribution I suppose
- border: minimal distance between squares
- minSize: minimal square size
- roundness: oh, this was accidental and fun, so it is included

There will be more.
Probably #87, #88, #89, #90 and #91
No ETA, no promises, don't know what differences will bring the future, but believing in the best.

27 May 2022 // NEURAL HAZE
